docs.lead_paragraph: THIS summer, Keith McGlinchey's has seen his business increase substantially. One assignment alone involved removing 45 raccoons that had infiltrated a pool-maintenance house at a beach club. Mr. McGlinchey is a state nuisance wildlife control agent or, more simply, a trapper. He is 1 of 17 in the county who have passed tests to be licensed by the Department of Environmental Conservation to remove wild animals from backyards, cellars, attics and garages.

headline.main: Homeowners React to Spread of Rabies
